==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penitence
<hw>Pen"i*tence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧nitence</ets>, L. <ets>paenitentia</ets>. See
<er>Penitent</er>, and cf. <er>Penance</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or
condition of being penitent; the disposition of a penitent; sorrow for
sins or faults; repentance; contrition.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Penitence</xex> of his old guilt.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Death is deferred, and <qex>penitenance</qex> has room⟦br⟧
To mitigate, if not reverse, the doom.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Repentance; contrition; compunction.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penitencer</ent>⟦br⟧
